{"key":"processedPost-10983268","value":{"id":10983268,"first":10982788,"last":10983418,"when":1251866508,"utime":"09/02/09 07:41 AM","content":"You can use perlite in casing layers, but most growers don't case, especially if growing cubensis.&nbsp; However, whether you use it or not, perlite and vermiculite are not the same thing at all.&nbsp; Perlite is like glass, being a crystalline mineral, and doesn't absorb water.&nbsp; Vermiculite is like a mineral sponge, absorbing many times its weight in water.&nbsp; Take a look at this thread which explains <a href=\"/forums/showflat.php/Number/6610766#6610766\" class=\"pp\" target=\"_blank\">the difference between perlite and vermiculite.</a><br />RR","title":"Re: Can I replace vermiculite with perlite?"}}